      "justification": "This error invalidates the quantitative interpretation of the 0.47% figure. The probability that a random, Koide-satisfying triple also yields a Soddy curvature near a quark mass is not the probability of observing the entire phenomenon by chance. The appropriate null would be the chance of finding *both* a Koide-like triple AND the quark match from a spectrum with no pre-imposed relations. The current setup artificially deflates the hit rate by preselecting for one unusual property (Koide saturation), making the subsequent coincidence seem rarer than it is in a fully random search."
