      "justification": "If corrected, this would materially increase the observed 'hit fraction' in the Monte Carlo, weakening the claim of rarity. Failing to account for the multiple comparisons across quark species, even if only one yields a hit in this instance, is a standard multiple testing error. The inference is based on a selected outcome without penalizing the selection process."
    },
