      "finding": "The parameter ranges and prior (log-uniform) for the Monte Carlo are arbitrary and influential. The hit rate is shown to vary by a factor of ~2 based on prior choice. The choice of a log-uniform prior over specific decades ([10^0,10^4] MeV for m3) is not justified by a physical null model. Mass spectra might follow different distributions (e.g., roughly geometric). The result's sensitivity to these arbitrary choices undermines any quantitative claim, even the conditional one the authors attempt to make.",
