      "finding": "The Monte Carlo null prior over Koide-conditioned triples is ad hoc and not physically justified. Sampling m3 log-uniformly on [10^0,10^4] MeV and m1 log-uniformly on [10^-3,10^-1]·m3, then solving for m2, imposes a very specific geometry on the space of Koide triples. The rarity estimate is therefore highly prior-dependent, and the limited prior-sensitivity check reported does not establish robustness to the much broader class of plausible reference measures.",
